result.execSummary:
The defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jorge Kenneth Cisneros is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jorge Kenneth Cisneros was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Jorge Kenneth Cisneros was found guilty of Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).
  • Jorge Kenneth Cisneros was found guilty of Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • Jorge Kenneth Cisneros was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Jorge Kenneth Cisneros was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must obtain his GED. 

The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.
The defendant must not consume or possess alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns.
The defendant must submit a DNA sample with surcharge assessed.

The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

The defendant must attend at least two AA meetings per week and is to provide proof of attendance to his P&P agent.

The defendant is to attend and successfully complete an inpatient treatment program for alcohol, drug and dual diagnosis and follow thru with all recommendations.

The defendant must successfully complete any aftercare of AODA following his inpatient treatment.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in court with attorney Mary L. Roth Burns.  Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Also called 14CF108 and 15CF147. Called at 10:48. Counsel has received PSI's, no errors or ommissions on PSI's noted. Court has reviewed the PSI's. State - received information on credit - 14CF108 - 6 days credit, 14CF94 - 4 days credit, 15CF147 - 163 days applied pending on how the court rules for stated reasons - State makes argument prior to sentencing - recommends on 14CF94 - count #1 - 6 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of ES, - will make consecutive argument but concurent to each other; 14CF108 - count #4 - 5 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 2 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of ES - consecutive to 14CF94; on 15CF147 - #1 - 9 months - concurrent to 14CF108, count #2 - 90 days - concurrent to count #1, count #3 - 3.5 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 1.5 years of initial confinement followed by 2 years of ES, counts #5 and #6 - 6 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of ES - concurrent to each other but consecutive to 14CF94. Court clarifies State's sentence recommendations. Burns makes final argument prior to sentencing - recommends 9-12 months of incarceration followed by probation (as PSI recommends). Defendant makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 14CF94 - 4 years in WI State Prison System consisting of 2 years of initial confinement followed by 2 years of ES; 14CF108 - 6 years in WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of intial confinement followed by 3 of ES - stayed - place on probation for 3 years - consecutive to sentence on 14CF94; 15CF147 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 3 years, consecutive to sentence on 14CF94, conditions of ES and probation:  AODA and follow thru, attend and successful complete a inpatient treatment program for alcohol, drug and dual diagnosis and follow thru with all recommendations and successfully complete any aftercare of AODA following his inpatient treatment, attend at least 2 AA meeting each week and submit proof of attendance to P&P agent, obtain GED, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns; fine on 14CF94 of $3000.00 plus costs - probation to be extended until fine is paid in full; credit on 14CF94 - 6 days; 14CF108 and 15CF147 - sentences are concurrent to each other but consecutive to 14CF94 - 167 days credit on 14CF108 and 15CF147 if revoked, revoke license for 3 years on 14CF94, IID on any vehicles titled in his name and DL for 3 years commencing upon issuance of a valid DL, costs on each count in other cases, submit DNA sample with expunction rights, no possession of firearms, no voting rights, not eligible for earned release programs, right to appeal, adjourned.
Sentencing hearing on May 13, 2016 at 10:00 am.
Sentencing hearing on May 12, 2016 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in court with attorney Mary L. Roth Burns.  Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:07 AM. Called 14CF94, 15CF147 and 14CF108. State - resolved - defense will ask for PSI with both parties free to aruge and State has no objection to the request of the PSI, 14CF94 - plead G to count #1, dismiss #2; 14CF108 - plead to count #4 and remaining counts DRI - have complied with victim notification requirement with restitution of $66.00 owed to victim (without VW surcharge), 15CF147 - dismiss count #4, plead G to counts #1, #2, #3, #5 and #6. Burns agrees except for she thought that the State was bound by the recommendation of the PSI. State disagrees. Recess to talk to client (9:09 AM). Back on record at 9:12 AM. Burns has discussed the difference with her client and they are still willing to proceed today. Cisneros agrees. Court - 14CF108 - DRI counts #1, #2 and #3, Cisneros pleads G to count #4 as alleged; 15CF147 - court dismisses count #4, Cisneros pleads G to counts #1, #2, #3, #5 and #6 - all as alleged; 14CF94 - dismiss count #2 and Cisneros pleads G to count #1 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty. State does not object to PSI and asks that he be remanded to FOSO until sentencing. Burns requests PSI. Court makes statement in regards to request for PSI. Court will order a PSI, remands to FOSO, sets for sentencing hearing  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 12, 2016 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in court with attorney Mary L. Roth Burns.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 3:10 PM. Called 14CF94, 14CF108, 15CF147. Burns has resolution on 2 cases and 15CF147 one of the counts they do not have an agreement on. Burns asks for adjournment to allow time to talk with DA. Off record, 3:12 PM. Back on the record, 3:15 PM. Court will adjourn. Bond continued.  Final pre-trial scheduled for March 9, 2016 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in court with attorney Mary L.R. Burns.  Defendant Jorge Kenneth Cisneros in custody.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 3:04 PM. Also called 14CF108 and 15CF147. State - believes 15CF147 will be a waiver of PH and the defendant will be pleading on 14CF94 and 14CF108. Burns and Cisneros agree. Court has waiver of PH form, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his right to PH, finds probable cause, binds over for trial. State has filed Information that mirrors the complaint. Burns has Information, waives reading of it, will proceed to ARGN and enters NG pleas to all counts. Court accepts pleas, continues bond and prior to setting for further proceedings, Court asks about the other cases. Burns states issues with going forward today with the plea on 14CF94 and 14CF108. Court understands. Court sets all matters for FPT. Court continues bond on all three matters.  Final pre-trial scheduled for February 17, 2016 at 02:15 pm.
